113 the county of residence of the victim or defendant.
114 (d) A person charged under this section shall be tried
115 as an adult and the record of the proceeding shall not be
116 sealed nor subject to expungement.
117 (e) It shall not be a defense to prosecution under this
118 section that an undercover operative or law enforcement
119 officer was involved in the detection and investigation of an
120 offense.
121 (f)(e) Transmitting obscene material of engaging in
122 sexual intercourse, sodomy, or to engage in a sexual
123 performance, obscene sexual performance, or sexual conduct for
124 his or her benefit to a child A violation of this section is a
125 Class B felony."
